      <text><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p>
<h3> </h3>
<h3>Exercise 2: Question Time</h3>
<p>Write a simple C program that prompts the user a series of questions:</p>
<p></p>
<ul>
<li>What is your name?</li>
<li>How old are you?</li>
<li>What is your favourite animal?</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>The answers should be safely stored in three variables and then printed to the screen in the form of a sentence that includes each of the answers.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Save your code in a file called <strong>exercise02.c</strong></p>
<p>You can use any text editor you like to create the file, but it must compile and run using the following commands (on the terminal of a University Linux machine):</p>
<pre>gcc exercise02.c -pedantic -Wall -o exercise02<br>./exercise02</pre>
<p>Attempt the quiz when your code is working to receive your mark</p>
<p>If you think this quiz is behaving incorrectly, speak to Andrew or email him (andrew.fagan@strath.ac.uk)</p>]]></text>
